<TITLE> Bush cuts tours of duty in Iraq to 12 months </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Washington, April 10 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - President George W. Bush on Thursday said he was reducing the military combat tours of duty in Iraq and Afghanistan to one year from 15 months. "To ease the burden on our troops and their families, I have directed the Secretary of Defense to reduce deployment lengths from 15 months to 12 months," he said. The changes would be effective for troops deploying starting Aug. 1.
